12/03/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- The public has been inconvenienced by a wave of strikes this week, as a growing number of state and private sector employees join protests against the government's planned reform of the pension system. Debate on the disputed reform bill began in parliament Tuesday (March 11th), the same day bank employees announced a 24-hour strike. Lawyers, medical staff, engineers and pharmacists are off the job Wednesday, while Athens' subway will be closed on Thursday. Protests by employees of the Public Power Corporation have resulted in power cuts throughout the country. (Sky, BTA - 12/03/08)
